OL,3,CSouthport killer's dad hears of
OL,4,C'complete disdain' from victims'
OL,5,Cfamilies
OL,7,F"All three parents have listened to
OL,8,Fwhat you have written, they have
OL,9,Flistened to what you have said and
OL,10,Fthey have complete disdain for your
OL,11,Fexcuses and the manner in which you
OL,12,Fhave answered questions."
OL,14,FMr Bowen was then cut off by the
OL,15,Finquiry chair Sir Adrian Fulford who
OL,16,Fsaid the comment was not appropriate.
OL,18,FWhen asked by Mr Bowen if there was
OL,19,Fanything he wanted to say to the
OL,20,Fparents the dad said he cried for them.
OL,26,@oD@AOUtD@YO]
