OL,3,CSouthport killer's dad hears of
OL,4,C'complete disdain' from victims'
OL,5,Cfamilies
OL,7,FHe said: "I cry for them all the time
OL,8,Fbecause I have a reminder (of) my son
OL,9,Fwho turned to be a monster.
OL,11,F"When I cry for him I remember them
OL,12,Fand cry for them.
OL,14,F"I'm so ashamed. I lost the courage to
OL,15,Fsave their little angels. I'm so
OL,16,Fsorry."
OL,18,FHe said he still loved his son "so
OL,19,Fmuch" and told the inquiry: "I know he
OL,20,Fis dangerous but he is my son."
